The paper deals with visual attribute transfer across images, which is a problem in computer vision. The paper proposes a new technique that uses deep convolutional neural networks for matching and finds semantically-meaningful dense correspondences between two input images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with image analogy, which is a technique used in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, such as deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
